investigation.title: Influence of Sex Hormones on Nervous System and Musculoskeletal Health in Micro and Martian Fractional Gravity in Rat Analogues (Force Plate; Soleus)
investigation.description: Gonadal hormones, such as testosterone and estradiol, modulate muscle size and strength in males and females. However, the influence of sex hormones on muscle strength in micro- and partial-gravity environments (e.g., the Moon or Mars) is not fully understood.

project.title: OS-891
